dismissalComment.html: Chanderpaul, the first-match hero for West Indies, is gone! Umpire Asad Rauf withhelds the appeal after a delay. It was a full-length delivery, slanting away outside the off stump, Chanderpaul lunges at it, has a poke and is beaten. The ball appeared to have brushed his back-pad enroute to Haddin, who dived low to his left to take it. but did it touch the bat. Shall report after I get a good look at the replays.

commentTextItems.html: Bravo dances down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball, drives it to mid-on and before the throw comes in, they cross over for the matchwinning single. West Indies win by three wickets and they are almost ensured of a place in the finals.

commentPostTextItems.html: Phew! What drama as Australia fought back hard and almost stormed their way back into the game. West Indies were coasting at one point but then contrived to lose a few wickets in a heap, raising blood pressures across the Caribbean before Dwayne Bravo, displaying a cool head, steered them home.
Join us on September 20 for the India v West Indies encounter. Please click here to have a look at the points table.

But with Samuels walking out and Dwayne Smith and Baugh still in , West Indies should wrap this up but ....
